  <!-- SECTION 7: Concentrated Liquidity Management -->
  <h2>Concentrated Liquidity Management on Solana</h2>

  <p>Concentrated liquidity is the primary yield driver on Orca and Meteora. Here&#8217;s how to manage it effectively.</p>

  <h3>Orca Whirlpools: Setting Your Price Range</h3>

  <p>When you create an Orca Whirlpool position, you choose a minimum and maximum price. The narrower your range, the higher your capital efficiency &#8212; but the more frequently you&#8217;ll need to rebalance.</p>

  <div class="glass-card">
    <p><strong>Orca Range Strategy Cheat Sheet:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Wide range (&plusmn;50%):</strong> Low IL, low capital efficiency (~2&#8211;3x vs. full range), minimal rebalancing</li>
      <li><strong>Medium range (&plusmn;20%):</strong> Moderate IL, 5&#8211;8x capital efficiency, rebalance every 1&#8211;2 weeks</li>
      <li><strong>Narrow range (&plusmn;5&#8211;10%):</strong> High IL risk, 10&#8211;20x capital efficiency, rebalance every 2&#8211;3 days</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Meteora DLMM: Multi-Bin Liquidity Distribution</h3>

  <p>Meteora&#8217;s DLMM allows you to distribute your capital across multiple discrete price bins within a range. Each bin operates as its own mini-pool with a configurable fee tier. Advanced LPs can:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Weight bins toward the current price:</strong> Allocate more capital to bins nearest the current market price to maximize fee capture</li>
    <li><strong>Use asymmetric fee tiers:</strong> Set higher fees on high-volatility bins and lower fees on stable-range bins</li>
    <li><strong>Leverage auto-compounding:</strong> Meteora&#8217;s built-in auto-compound feature reinvests fees into the position automatically</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Use tools like <a href="https://www.orca.so" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Orca&#8217;s position tracker</a> or <a href="https://app.meteora.ag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meteora&#8217;s analytics dashboard</a> to monitor your concentrated positions. Set price alerts within 5% of your range boundaries to avoid getting fully converted to one token.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 8: APR/APY Calculation -->
  <h2>APR vs APY: What Your Yield Numbers Actually Mean</h2>

  <p>This distinction matters more than most LPs realize. Here&#8217;s the difference and how to calculate both.</p>

  <div class="glass-card">
    <p><strong>APR (Annual Percentage Rate)</strong> is the simple annual return without compounding. If a pool shows 40% APR and you earn fees linearly, you&#8217;ll receive approximately 3.33% per month.</p>
    <p><strong>APY (Annual Percentage Yield)</strong> includes the effect of compounding. If fees are auto-compounded daily, the same 40% APR becomes approximately <strong>49.1% APY</strong> &#8212; nearly 10 percentage points higher.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="formula-box">
    APY = (1 + APR / n)<sup>n</sup> &#8722; 1 &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; n = compounding periods per year
  </div>

  <p>Real-world example for a Meteora DLMM position earning 75% APR with daily auto-compounding:</p>

  <div class="glass-card">
    <ul>
      <li>Simple APR: 75%</li>
      <li>Daily compounding (365 periods): APY = (1 + 0.75/365)<sup>365</sup> &#8722; 1 = <strong>111.7%</strong></li>
      <li>Weekly compounding (52 periods): APY = (1 + 0.75/52)<sup>52</sup> &#8722; 1 = <strong>109.3%</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>Always check whether a platform displays APR or APY. Raydium typically shows APR (no auto-compound in most pools). Meteora shows APY for Dynamic Vaults (built-in auto-compound). Orca shows APR for base LP positions (manual compound through harvest and redeposit).</p>

  <!-- SECTION 9: Risk Assessment -->
  <h2>Risk Assessment: What Every Solana LP Must Evaluate</h2>

  <p>Yield is only half the equation. Here&#8217;s the comprehensive risk framework every LP should apply before depositing.</p>

  <div class="protocol-card">
    <h4>1. Impermanent Loss <span class="score-badge score-med">Medium Risk</span></h4>
    <p>Already covered in detail above. Key mitigants: use correlated pairs, concentrated liquidity with tight ranges only if you&#8217;re actively managing, and avoid volatile memecoin pairs for long-term positions.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="protocol-card">
    <h4>2. Smart Contract Risk <span class="score-badge score-med">Medium Risk</span></h4>
    <p>Raydium, Orca, and Meteora have all been audited by top-tier firms (Neodyme, Halborn, Kudelski). However, DeFi exploits remain a concern in 2026. Mitigations: use protocols with &gt;12 months of proven TVL, check for recent audits, and never deposit funds you can&#8217;t afford to lose. Consider using Meteora Dynamic Vaults which add an additional layer of risk isolation.</p>
    <div class="affiliate-box">
      <p><strong>Hardware Security:</strong> Protect your LP funds with a hardware wallet. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0B2L7VSP5/?tag=dogeking03-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ledger Nano X</a> offers wireless connectivity and supports all Solana DEXs. For a budget option, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07Y3Y3T8J/?tag=dogeking03-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ledger Nano S Plus</a> provides the same security at a lower price point.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="protocol-card">
    <h4>3. Token Volatility Risk <span class="score-badge score-low">High Risk</span></h4>
    <p>The underlying tokens in your LP pair can dump 50&#8211;90% rapidly. This is separate from IL &#8212; it&#8217;s the outright loss of principal due to token depreciation. Mitigations: prioritize blue-chip pairs (SOL, USDC, mSOL, JitoSOL), limit exposure to small-cap tokens, and set a maximum allocation per pool (e.g., no more than 10% of your portfolio in any single pool).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="protocol-card">
    <h4>4. Liquidity and Slippage Risk <span class="score-badge score-med">Medium Risk</span></h4>
    <p>Low-TVL pools can have high slippage when you enter or exit positions. Always check pool depth before depositing. Raydium&#8217;s blue-chip pools typically have $5M+ in liquidity; Meteora DLMM pools may have $100K&#8211;$1M depending on the pair.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="protocol-card">
    <h4>5. Regulatory and Tax Risk <span class="score-badge score-med">Medium Risk</span></h4>
    <p>Every LP deposit, withdrawal, fee harvest, and token conversion is a taxable event in most jurisdictions. Track everything. Pools that distribute reward tokens create additional tax lots. Use automated tax tools like <a href="https://www.cointracker.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CoinTracker</a> or <a href="https://koinly.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Koinly</a> to stay compliant.</p>
  </div>

